properties.Title: Heat Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A long duration heat event is expected. Daytime high temperatures in the low thirties with overnight lows near 18 are expected until the end of this week. Please refer to your public forecast for further details on expected temperatures. Hot and humid air can also bring deteriorating air quality and can result in the Air Quality Health Index to approach the high risk category. ### Extreme heat affects everyone. The risks are greater for young children, pregnant women, older adults, people with chronic illnesses and people working or exercising outdoors. Watch for the effects of heat illness: swelling, rash, cramps, fainting, heat exhaustion, heat stroke and the worsening of some health conditions. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
Expires: 2020-06-29T20:11:03-00:00

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: At 2:27 a.m. CDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm capable of producing heavy rain. A slow moving area of thunderstorms is located from Minnedosa to McCreary. This area of thunderstorms is moving northeast at approximately 30 km/h. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Intense lightning is likely with any thunderstorm that develops. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.
Expires: 2020-06-29T09:26:51-00:00

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of dangerous thunderstorms that may be capable of producing strong wind gusts, large hail and torrential rain. Thunderstorms continue over portions of southwestern Manitoba and the Interlake late this evening. Some of these thunderstorms may reach severe limits. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to MBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #MBStorm.

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Conditions are favourable for the development of dangerous thunderstorms that may be capable of producing strong wind gusts, large hail and torrential rain. A stationary front is triggering scattered thunderstorms over western Manitoba this evening. Some of these thunderstorms may reach severe limits. Thunderstorms are expected to redevelop across much of the watch area later this afternoon and will persist well into the night. This severe thunderstorm watch may be expanded eastwards this afternoon as the event unfolds. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Severe thunderstorm watches are issued when atmospheric conditions are favourable for the development of thunderstorms that could produce one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to MBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #MBStorm.
